result.execSummary:
The defendant Kourtney Marie Moore was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Misappropriate ID Info - Obtain Money, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.201(2)(a).
  • Misappropriate ID Info - Obtain Money, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.201(2)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Defendant Kourtney Marie Moore in court with Attorney Joseph R Kennedy.  Defendant Kourtney Marie Moore in custody.  Michael Jerome Lonski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Sentencing proceeds.  State has complied with victim notification.  Statements by the State, defense counsel, and defendant.   COURT ADVISES the defendant she must provide a DNA sample and pay the DNA surcharge.  

As to Count 1:
COURT ORDERS defendant to serve a term in the Wisconsin State Prison system - TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE -  54  months with  177 days credit;  -  INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT -   18 months  -  EXTENDED SUPERVISION -  36 months

As to Count 2:
COURT ORDERS defendant to serve a term in the Wisconsin State Prison system - TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE -  54  months with  177 days credit; CONCURRENT to the sentence imposed as to Count 1;  -  INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT -   18 months  -  EXTENDED SUPERVISION -  36 months

- Court sets Restitution in the amount of $0  (Zero)

Court finds defendant IS eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program but is NOT eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:  
-  Seek/Maintain full-time employment or a combination of part-time employment and school
-  No contact with the victims (Donald L., Philip B., Shawn V., and Rafael M.)
-  No weapons of any kind
-  No fine
-  Pay the costs, fees, assessments and surcharges (including the DNA surcharge) during the term of extended supervision.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.

NOTE:  Extended Supervision may be transferred to the State of California

COURT ORDERS:
-  defendant to provide a biological specimen for DNA analysis, if not already done so
-  DOC to collect monetary sums/amounts at the rate of 25% of prison funds.
